berlin for Debian
----------------------

From the website:

Berlin is a windowing system being
actively developed by members of the free
software community. Its features include a
multilingual text rendering system, a set
of extensible user interface components
residing in-process with the display server,
an advanced imaging model with strong support
for hardware acceleration, and a
persistent user-preferences database. 

Berlin is designed around 3 major existing
standards: Unicode, OpenGL, and Corba. It
is released under the GNU Library General
Public License, and written entirely by
volunteers using GNU/Linux, OmniORB, Mesa and
Egcs -- all free software. 

